          description : "2.2.1.2 Ensure ntp is configured - restrict -4"
          info        : "'ntp' is a daemon which implements the Network Time Protocol (NTP). It is designed to synchronize system clocks across a variety of systems and use a source that is highly accurate. More information on NTP can be found at [http://www.ntp.org](http://www.ntp.org/). 'ntp' can be configured to be a client and/or a server.

